<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-5129] Swift TSocketTransport cannot be used to connect to client</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5129</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TLDR; Swift library cannot be used to connect to a client using TSocketTransport with present code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In TSocketTransport init, socket IP is not set for non-linux systems, so TSocketTransport cannot be used to connect clients.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is set as: `in_addr(s_addr: in_addr_t(0))` in line TSocketTransport.swift 162.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; addr = sockaddr_in(sin_len: UInt8(MemoryLayout&amp;lt;sockaddr_in&amp;gt;.size),
                       sin_family: sa_family_t(AF_INET),
                       sin_port: in_port_t(htons(UInt16(port))),
                       sin_addr: in_addr(s_addr: in_addr_t(0)),
                       sin_zero: (0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
